cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper is about machine learning and information theory, specifically about selecting the best information divergence for a given learning task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions Nonnegative Matrix/Tensor Factorization, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and Bayesian network optimization, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
